1
00:01:31,370 --> 00:01:34,720
[Silent Tides]

2
00:01:35,259 --> 00:01:37,979
[Episode 21]

3
00:01:39,180 --> 00:01:40,440
Everyone, please give

4
00:01:41,340 --> 00:01:44,600
a warm welcome to Miss Qiao
for her wonderful performance.

5
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:06,040
Okay, everyone.

6
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,560
Next, let's welcome Miss Qiao

7
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:10,090
to perform "Tzigane" for us.

8
00:02:10,090 --> 00:02:11,240
A round of applause!

9
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,280
Yinwan.

10
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:57,410
Xian.

11
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,250
What on earth is going on?

12
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:02,050
Why are you at Bachongtian Club?

13
00:04:03,210 --> 00:04:04,370
I forgot to tell you

14
00:04:05,130 --> 00:04:06,680
that I've resigned
from Kiang Wu Elementary School

15
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,610
and returned to Bachongtian Club.

16
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:09,370
Why?

17
00:04:11,010 --> 00:04:12,610
I was always a violin player,

18
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,130
and the salary here is much higher.

19
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:16,950
Would you really come back
to Bachongtian Club for a higher salary?

20
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:18,370
The Special Operations Team is
right upstairs.

21
00:04:18,370 --> 00:04:20,100
You're jumping into a fire pit!

22
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:21,029
Come with me.

23
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:25,590
Miss Qiao,

24
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:26,770
h-here's the thing...

25
00:04:26,770 --> 00:04:28,240
Your performance just now was

26
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,130
absolutely stunning

27
00:04:30,130 --> 00:04:31,510
and breathtaking.

28
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:33,180
Colonel Sawa Eisaku
of the Japanese Imperial Army is

29
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:34,010
specially sending

30
00:04:34,010 --> 00:04:35,470
this flower basket to you.

31
00:04:41,450 --> 00:04:44,510
Dr. Lok Pak,
you truly have an eye for talent.

32
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,720
Bachongtian Club

33
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:50,860
got an artist like Miss Qiao,

34
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:53,390
so we are fortunate tonight

35
00:04:54,130 --> 00:04:56,460
to feast our ears on such beautiful music.

36
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:02,880
And he's rewarding you with 10 gold bars.

37
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:08,860
Dr. Lok Pak,

38
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,370
please pass these on

39
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:14,250
to Miss Qiao.

40
00:05:16,930 --> 00:05:17,600
Thank you.

41
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:21,840
Thank you for your kindness,
Agency Chief Sawa.

42
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:43,920
Chief,

43
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,460
why did this woman, Qiao,

44
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,870
have to come to Bachongtian Club

45
00:05:47,870 --> 00:05:49,420
instead of anywhere else?

46
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:51,310
She came here just to go against us!

47
00:05:51,310 --> 00:05:52,500
What kind of trouble

48
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:54,570
could a woman possibly stir up?

49
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,070
Didn't you say

50
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:00,800
that the money was for Lok Pak?

51
00:06:00,990 --> 00:06:02,390
Why did you give it to her?

52
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,750
Weren't you being too generous with her?

53
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:05,150
Did I do this for her sake?

54
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,940
You were showing some respect to Lok Pak.

55
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:12,550
Then you know what to do, huh?

56
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:16,620
I promise

57
00:06:16,650 --> 00:06:18,330
that I won't let something like this

58
00:06:18,330 --> 00:06:19,680
happen again.

59
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,330
Also,

60
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:23,490
weren't you supposed
to be monitoring He Xian?

61
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:25,500
He Xian came to find Lok Pak.

62
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:27,840
Why haven't I heard your report?

63
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:31,660
Chief,

64
00:06:31,690 --> 00:06:33,950
we usually report the surveillance results

65
00:06:33,950 --> 00:06:35,830
to you the next day, right?

66
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:37,010
We haven't had time yet...

67
00:06:37,010 --> 00:06:38,450
Don't make excuses!

68
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:41,450
Keep a close eye on He Xian

69
00:06:42,690 --> 00:06:44,340
and report to me immediately.

70
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:45,540
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

71
00:06:45,909 --> 00:06:47,450
Why didn't you tell me that Yinwan

72
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:48,830
had returned to Bachongtian Club?

73
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:50,830
I was just about to tell you.

74
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:52,500
Then why didn't you stop her?

75
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,720
I can't be more delighted
at Yinwan's return to Bachongtian Club.

76
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:56,850
Why would I stop her?

77
00:06:58,450 --> 00:07:00,120
The Special Operations Team is
right upstairs,

78
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,370
yet she's back here,

79
00:07:01,370 --> 00:07:03,500
smiling while saying thank you
to Sawa Eisaku.

80
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,900
Don't you wonder why?

81
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:06,950
Why?

82
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:09,030
To avenge her brother's death.

83
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:12,920
No way.

84
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,800
I must persuade her to leave.

85
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,830
It's too dangerous for her to stay here.

86
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:16,630
In my opinion,

87
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,420
letting Yinwan stay
in Kiang Wu to hang around

88
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:20,370
with Principal Liang,

89
00:07:20,370 --> 00:07:21,900
and especially with you, is

90
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:23,320
what's truly dangerous.

91
00:07:24,890 --> 00:07:26,570
Yinwan decided to come back

92
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,260
to Bachongtian Club herself.

93
00:07:28,330 --> 00:07:29,330
As for her safety,

94
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,740
you just saw it yourself.

95
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:33,000
With me around, no one dares to touch her.

96
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,940
I'd like to suggest you

97
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,820
not forget your position.

98
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:37,990
From now on,

99
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:40,120
try to contact Yinwan less often.

100
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,250
What do you mean by this?

101
00:07:43,340 --> 00:07:44,600
As I told you just now,

102
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,920
you also know very well

103
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,560
that you're on the Japanese

104
00:07:47,590 --> 00:07:49,070
priority watch list.

105
00:07:58,970 --> 00:07:59,700
Wanqi.

106
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,890
What?

107
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,160
Do I look bad in this?

108
00:08:19,870 --> 00:08:20,400
No.

109
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:23,470
I just don't understand
why you're doing this.

110
00:08:23,830 --> 00:08:24,660
I was thinking

111
00:08:25,220 --> 00:08:26,450
that no matter how severe
your pneumonia is,

112
00:08:26,450 --> 00:08:28,250
you'll recover in a month or two.

113
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,010
When you've recovered,

114
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,660
spring will be coming.

115
00:08:32,370 --> 00:08:33,700
While you have time,

116
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:38,380
let's hold our wedding, shall we?

117
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:40,679
I know you're busy

118
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:42,169
and don't have time
for these trivial matters.

119
00:08:42,169 --> 00:08:44,030
I'll arrange everything.

120
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:45,680
It won't take up your time.

121
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:53,860
What's wrong?

122
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:56,870
Did I do something wrong?

123
00:09:05,830 --> 00:09:06,450
Baixin,

124
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,900
take a look at these first.

125
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:17,610
These are all enrollment ads
from foreign universities.

126
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:19,290
Why are you showing me these?

127
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:20,410
Didn't you want

128
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:21,720
to study before?

129
00:09:24,050 --> 00:09:25,450
Now Hong Kong has fallen.

130
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:27,750
Macau isn't safe, either.

131
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,210
If you want to study,

132
00:09:29,370 --> 00:09:30,630
you can only go abroad.

133
00:09:31,930 --> 00:09:33,790
These schools are all quite good.

134
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:35,230
Take your time to choose

135
00:09:36,090 --> 00:09:37,820
and see if any of them suits you.

136
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:51,200
Wanqi.

137
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,260
Are you trying to send me away?

138
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:10,710
Tell Ms Ming once you've made your choice.

139
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:13,570
I've given her money
for your travel and tuition.

140
00:10:13,570 --> 00:10:15,030
There's no need to tell me.

141
00:10:41,210 --> 00:10:41,770
Yinwan,

142
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:42,790
come with me.

143
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:48,150
Xian.

144
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:49,890
What's wrong?

145
00:10:49,890 --> 00:10:50,950
What's the matter?

146
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,220
Yinwan,

147
00:10:53,670 --> 00:10:55,270
I know you hate the Japanese.

148
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:57,050
You came to Bachongtian Club

149
00:10:57,050 --> 00:10:59,250
to find a chance to avenge your brother.

150
00:10:59,650 --> 00:11:02,500
But Agency Chief Sawa's men are
professional intelligence agents.

151
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,450
How can you

152
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:05,320
fight against them alone?

153
00:11:10,330 --> 00:11:11,660
This is my own business.

154
00:11:12,450 --> 00:11:14,250
The Japanese killed my brother.

155
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,530
They killed so many of our people.

156
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:19,650
Now I have a chance

157
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:21,430
to get close to them

158
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:24,030
and try my best to gather information

159
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:26,760
to prevent more people
from being harmed by them.

160
00:11:27,430 --> 00:11:28,690
If you were in my place,

161
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:32,460
you would do the same, wouldn't you?

162
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:33,840
Yinwan.

163
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:36,340
I understand how you feel.

164
00:11:36,850 --> 00:11:39,110
But it's really dangerous for you to stay

165
00:11:39,410 --> 00:11:40,940
at Bachongtian Club alone.

166
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:42,490
So what if it's dangerous?

167
00:11:43,060 --> 00:11:44,720
Weren't you also risking your life

168
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,380
to steal the printing plates?

169
00:11:48,210 --> 00:11:49,870
When I learned from my brother

170
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:53,810
that the printing plates were hidden
in the orphanage,

171
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:56,200
and that my task was

172
00:11:57,050 --> 00:11:58,370
to play that melody

173
00:11:58,370 --> 00:11:59,830
to pass the message to you,

174
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:01,620
I hesitated.

175
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:06,280
I didn't know
if I should play that melody.

176
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:11,180
Why?

177
00:12:13,510 --> 00:12:15,110
Because I saw with my own eyes

178
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:16,870
that the place had become

179
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:18,270
the Japanese Naval Club.

180
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,350
And I also knew

181
00:12:22,630 --> 00:12:24,360
that once I played that melody,

182
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:26,740
no matter how dangerous the situation,

183
00:12:26,740 --> 00:12:27,580
you'd go there anyway,

184
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:29,180
even at the risk of your life.

185
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,480
Xian.

186
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:41,870
My brother taught me with his life

187
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:44,130
that great love is great righteousness.

188
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,930
So I must stay at Bachongtian Club.

189
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:01,310
[Hengqin Island]

190
00:13:01,310 --> 00:13:02,240
Wait, Uncle.

191
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:04,410
There must be some misunderstanding.

192
00:13:04,410 --> 00:13:06,250
Xian just came this morning
to discuss cooperation.

193
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:08,250
And both sides were pleased
with how it went.

194
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:09,740
Rodrigues may be a terrible person,

195
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:10,630
but if he had even a bit of sense,

196
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:11,650
he wouldn't do something like this

197
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:12,630
at such a critical moment,

198
00:13:12,630 --> 00:13:13,290
right?

199
00:13:13,290 --> 00:13:13,940
Zixia,

200
00:13:13,940 --> 00:13:15,130
I just have one question for you.

201
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:16,580
Was it Rodrigues' ship

202
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:18,630
that stopped your Uncle Zhong?

203
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:19,600
Yes.

204
00:13:19,630 --> 00:13:20,530
But...

205
00:13:20,530 --> 00:13:21,660
There are no "buts"!

206
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:23,520
What is

207
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:24,910
Rodrigues up to?

208
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:27,400
He used to bully our Tai Ho Brotherhood.

209
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,280
And today,

210
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,690
he's working with the Japanese,

211
00:13:29,690 --> 00:13:31,150
causing so much bloodshed

212
00:13:31,290 --> 00:13:32,090
among our men.

213
00:13:32,930 --> 00:13:34,090
Old grudges plus new hatred.

214
00:13:34,090 --> 00:13:35,560
If I don't seek revenge on him,

215
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:36,370
then who should I go after?

216
00:13:36,370 --> 00:13:36,890
You can have revenge,

217
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:37,360
Uncle.

218
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:39,410
But shouldn't we at least
inform Xian first?

219
00:13:39,410 --> 00:13:40,200
Zixia,

220
00:13:40,650 --> 00:13:42,580
haven't you heard the scout's report?

221
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:43,580
Tonight,

222
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:46,330
Rodrigues' ship will
deliver goods to Lyun Coeng.

223
00:13:46,330 --> 00:13:47,470
If we don't act now,

224
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:48,730
it will be too late!

225
00:13:49,170 --> 00:13:49,850
Everyone,

226
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:50,630
let's go!

227
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:51,750
Let's go!

228
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:52,250
Uncle...

229
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:52,840
Let's go!

230
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:59,840
As long as the Macau government
immediately prohibits

231
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:03,410
financial institutions
from underwriting Chinese government bonds

232
00:14:03,410 --> 00:14:06,670
and promptly bans
anti-Japanese propaganda activities,

233
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:10,320
the Japanese Imperial Army
will fully guarantee

234
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:13,290
all Portuguese merchants' navigation
and trading rights in Macau

235
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:17,720
and grant Portuguese merchants
in Macau the rights

236
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,790
to trade in materials
listed by the Imperial Army.

237
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:22,720
I hereby announce

238
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:25,230
that the Macau government
accepts the 2 bans

239
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:26,760
proposed by Japan.

240
00:14:28,150 --> 00:14:29,550
effective immediately.

241
00:14:30,190 --> 00:14:34,370
[Banco Nacional Ultramarino]

242
00:14:34,370 --> 00:14:35,720
Didn't Mr. Rodrigues say

243
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:36,780
where he was going?

244
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,800
He received a call this morning,

245
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:41,160
but he didn't tell me where he was going.

246
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:05,720
Hello?

247
00:15:06,170 --> 00:15:07,320
Is it Ho Hai Club?

248
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:08,840
This is He Xian.

249
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:11,630
I had an appointment
with Master Sanhe at 9,

250
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:13,470
but it's been half an hour now.

251
00:15:13,510 --> 00:15:14,440
Master Sanhe...

252
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:17,000
What?

253
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:19,480
Master Sanhe hasn't returned yet?

254
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:23,720
Okay.

255
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:24,980
Thank you.

256
00:15:37,050 --> 00:15:38,150
Mr. Rodrigues,

257
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,700
what happened?

258
00:15:41,090 --> 00:15:43,420
You have the nerve to ask me
what happened?

259
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:50,530
[Wartime Government Bonds]

260
00:15:50,530 --> 00:15:52,540
Hey, you there! Stop what you're doing!

261
00:15:52,540 --> 00:15:53,940
Take all their stuff!

262
00:15:57,250 --> 00:15:57,910
Don't take my things!

263
00:15:57,910 --> 00:15:59,740
Get back!

264
00:15:59,740 --> 00:16:00,680
Hands off!

265
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:01,840
Don't take my stuff!

266
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:03,410
Get back!

267
00:16:09,020 --> 00:16:12,740
[China Government Bonds
Available for Subscription]

268
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:18,070
Is the Governor really not here,

269
00:16:18,150 --> 00:16:19,800
or is he hiding to avoid us?

270
00:16:19,830 --> 00:16:20,960
Mr. Liang,

271
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,310
the Governor is really away for business.

272
00:16:24,110 --> 00:16:25,390
Mr. Liang,

273
00:16:25,410 --> 00:16:27,370
the bans have already been issued.

274
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:30,050
Even if you find
His Excellency the Governor,

275
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,970
there's nothing he can do now.

276
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:34,680
You're elderly.

277
00:16:34,710 --> 00:16:36,590
Please don't get too worked up.

278
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,530
Your health comes first.

279
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:47,580
What are you doing?

280
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:48,080
Let go!

281
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,580
By what right are you interfering
with the banks' normal business?

282
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:50,220
Stop it!

283
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:53,850
What are you doing?

284
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:56,450
We just received the government bans.

285
00:16:56,450 --> 00:16:58,070
All financial institutions in Macau are

286
00:16:58,070 --> 00:17:00,620
prohibited from underwriting
Chinese government bonds.

287
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:02,540
The General Economic Bureau is working
with the police

288
00:17:02,540 --> 00:17:04,339
to ban illegal business operations.

289
00:17:04,339 --> 00:17:05,300
Mr. Lok Pak,

290
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:08,329
what did you promise me last night?

291
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:10,280
Have you forgotten it so quickly?

292
00:17:10,410 --> 00:17:12,210
About what happened last night,

293
00:17:13,420 --> 00:17:14,280
I can't recall.

294
00:17:17,390 --> 00:17:19,730
I only know that the government bans are
now in effect.

295
00:17:19,730 --> 00:17:22,190
Any banking institution in Macau

296
00:17:22,210 --> 00:17:23,599
that defies the bans

297
00:17:23,630 --> 00:17:25,000
and continues illegal operations

298
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,000
will be shut down.

299
00:17:27,089 --> 00:17:27,810
Mr. He,

300
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,840
you now have two choices.

301
00:17:30,130 --> 00:17:32,330
Either you remove the sign yourself

302
00:17:32,690 --> 00:17:33,830
and stop the underwriting,

303
00:17:33,830 --> 00:17:35,180
or the police

304
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,930
will immediately shut down Tai Fung Bank.

305
00:17:52,620 --> 00:17:53,220
Mr. Liang.

306
00:17:57,340 --> 00:17:58,030
Mr. Liang.

307
00:18:05,850 --> 00:18:08,350
Let's just return the remaining bonds

308
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,540
immediately.

309
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:25,260
Mr. Liang,

310
00:18:26,090 --> 00:18:27,280
I'm truly sorry.

311
00:18:56,420 --> 00:18:57,440
[Wanted]

312
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,480
Mr. Rodrigues,

313
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:01,090
I heard that in the early morning

314
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:02,110
today,

315
00:19:02,110 --> 00:19:03,330
you were robbed

316
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,120
by the shameless pirates

317
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:07,140
and suffered considerable losses.

318
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:08,490
I'm calling you,

319
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:11,600
hoping you can give us a chance

320
00:19:12,210 --> 00:19:13,840
to make up for your losses.

321
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:15,440
What do you mean?

322
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:17,000
Are you going to help
the pirates compensate

323
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,600
for my ship and cargo losses?

324
00:19:19,770 --> 00:19:22,110
No, that's not what I meant.

325
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:24,680
However, we've learned

326
00:19:25,090 --> 00:19:26,590
that you have a shipment

327
00:19:27,010 --> 00:19:29,010
that will be arriving in Macau soon.

328
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:31,390
It includes large quantities

329
00:19:31,410 --> 00:19:33,480
of cotton fabric, rubber shoes,

330
00:19:34,330 --> 00:19:35,460
potassium nitrate,

331
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:38,920
Western medicine,
and various hardware products.

332
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,430
What exactly are you trying to say?

333
00:19:40,430 --> 00:19:42,780
I can introduce you to a premium client

334
00:19:42,810 --> 00:19:45,790
who will pay top dollar
for your incoming shipment to Macau.

335
00:19:45,790 --> 00:19:46,740
I'm so sorry,

336
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:47,880
but it's not convenient for me

337
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,840
to do business
with Japanese-funded companies right now.

338
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:52,350
The client I'm introducing is
the Great Chinese Union Trading Company,

339
00:19:52,350 --> 00:19:54,610
the one just established in Macau
by Mr. Wang Qizheng,

340
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:55,760
the brother-in-law

341
00:19:56,140 --> 00:19:59,900
of Zhongshan County Magistrate Lin Nianci.

342
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:01,320
It's fully owned by China

343
00:20:01,770 --> 00:20:03,900
and operated entirely by the Chinese.

344
00:20:03,930 --> 00:20:05,060
In other words,

345
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,160
the real boss

346
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:09,580
of the Great Chinese Union is
the Wang puppet government in Nanjing.

347
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:12,350
How is that any different
from your Japanese-funded firms?

348
00:20:12,350 --> 00:20:15,750
As long as it appears
to be Chinese-owned, isn't that enough?

349
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:17,890
Don't you agree?

350
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:27,170
[Fundraising for National Salvation]

351
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:37,220
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

352
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,990
The rise and fall of our nation is

353
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:43,790
every citizen's responsibility.

354
00:20:43,790 --> 00:20:44,390
Everyone,

355
00:20:45,130 --> 00:20:46,660
contribute money if you can;

356
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:48,590
contribute effort if you're able.

357
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:49,340
Thank you.

358
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,060
Thank you, guys.

359
00:20:58,290 --> 00:20:59,220
Mr. Liang?

360
00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:10,680
[Jinheyuan Sweet Soup]

361
00:21:16,010 --> 00:21:17,430
[Wanted]

362
00:21:38,290 --> 00:21:40,620
So it really was you
who hijacked the ship?

363
00:21:42,070 --> 00:21:42,570
Yes.

364
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,880
Uncle Sanehe insisted
on getting revenge,

365
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,210
and I couldn't stop him.

366
00:21:46,370 --> 00:21:48,000
Besides, it was indeed
Rodrigues' merchant ship

367
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:48,890
that started to act unjustly.

368
00:21:48,890 --> 00:21:49,880
He threw the first punch,

369
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,210
so we were in a position
to hit back, right?

370
00:21:53,310 --> 00:21:54,140
Where is

371
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:55,970
Master Sanhe now?

372
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:58,530
He's hiding at sea
with the ship and cargo.

373
00:21:58,530 --> 00:21:59,090
He sent me back

374
00:21:59,090 --> 00:22:00,380
to check the situation

375
00:22:00,570 --> 00:22:02,700
and also tell you about the hijacking.

376
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:06,510
But Rodrigues wasn't really
trying to mess with you.

377
00:22:06,510 --> 00:22:07,770
I sent Yang Chang

378
00:22:07,810 --> 00:22:09,480
to Hengqin last night

379
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:10,790
to explain everything to you.

380
00:22:10,790 --> 00:22:12,000
Why couldn't you just be patient

381
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:12,720
instead of acting so rashly?

382
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:13,590
Yang Chang?

383
00:22:14,660 --> 00:22:16,000
We never saw him at all.

384
00:22:28,310 --> 00:22:30,440
Xian, Dr. Ke.

385
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:33,470
Tell me where you were last night.

386
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:40,990
Last night...

387
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,570
Where on earth were you last night?

388
00:22:45,410 --> 00:22:45,420
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

389
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:46,580
Thank you, thank you.

390
00:22:46,580 --> 00:22:47,360
Okay.

391
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:50,060
Thank you, thank you so much.

392
00:22:50,810 --> 00:22:51,350
Alright.

393
00:22:52,130 --> 00:22:52,460
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

394
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:53,660
Thank you, thank you.

395
00:22:54,220 --> 00:22:54,820
Thank you.

396
00:22:55,420 --> 00:22:56,050
Okay.

397
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:58,000
Thank you.

398
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,030
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

399
00:23:00,030 --> 00:23:00,500
Thanks.

400
00:23:01,090 --> 00:23:03,290
This old gentleman is really stubborn.

401
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:06,160
Without
financial institutions' underwriting,

402
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:08,330
how many bucks can he make
with a street stall?

403
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:09,740
Isn't this just a waste of effort?

404
00:23:09,740 --> 00:23:10,640
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

405
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:11,240
Thank you.

406
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:12,800
This one...

407
00:23:13,460 --> 00:23:14,030
Thanks.

408
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:23,300
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

409
00:23:23,300 --> 00:23:23,900
Thank you.

410
00:23:33,140 --> 00:23:34,210
Mr. Rodrigues,

411
00:23:34,550 --> 00:23:35,680
let me introduce you

412
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:36,980
to this gentleman,

413
00:23:37,030 --> 00:23:37,120
[Wang Qizheng, Manager
of Great Chinese Union Trading Company]

414
00:23:37,120 --> 00:23:38,630
Mr. Wang Qizheng, the General Manager

415
00:23:38,630 --> 00:23:40,580
of Great Chinese Union Trading Company.

416
00:23:40,580 --> 00:23:41,840
Hello, Mr. Rodrigues.

417
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:49,930
It's such a high price.

418
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,500
Mr. Wang, you're so generous.

419
00:23:52,930 --> 00:23:54,520
Only with such a price

420
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:55,530
can we demonstrate

421
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:57,880
the Imperial Army's sincerity
in maintaining

422
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:59,880
Japanese-Portuguese friendship.

423
00:24:01,810 --> 00:24:04,400
That's right. And it's not just this time.

424
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:06,390
If you're willing to cooperate,

425
00:24:06,390 --> 00:24:09,240
we'll purchase all your future shipments,

426
00:24:09,260 --> 00:24:11,410
no matter the quantity.

427
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:13,530
And as for the price,

428
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,630
we'll keep it the same as this time.

429
00:24:16,770 --> 00:24:16,810
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

430
00:24:16,810 --> 00:24:18,010
Thank you, thank you.

431
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:19,070
Thank you.

432
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:20,660
Thank you.

433
00:24:22,180 --> 00:24:22,700
Get lost!

434
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:23,530
Thank you.

435
00:24:23,530 --> 00:24:24,330
Get lost!

436
00:24:28,830 --> 00:24:30,230
What are you trying to do?

437
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:32,380
The Macau government has just issued

438
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:34,570
a ban on selling Chinese government bonds.

439
00:24:34,570 --> 00:24:36,420
What do you think you're doing?

440
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:37,940
What am I doing?

441
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:39,790
Who are you anyway?

442
00:24:40,490 --> 00:24:42,490
Are you representing the Macau government

443
00:24:42,490 --> 00:24:43,780
or the Macau police?

444
00:24:44,620 --> 00:24:45,640
Listen carefully.

445
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:47,470
This is not what you can interfere with,

446
00:24:47,470 --> 00:24:48,890
you traitors.

447
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:50,010
Get lost.

448
00:25:05,830 --> 00:25:07,910
Fine! You're quite bold!

449
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:09,330
Today, I'll show you

450
00:25:09,330 --> 00:25:11,530
that I, Huang Gongjie, am a big shot
in Macau,

451
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:12,930
doing everything my way.

452
00:25:13,070 --> 00:25:15,010
Guys, smash everything!

453
00:25:15,270 --> 00:25:16,230
[Wartime Government Bond Sales Point]

454
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,250
[Underwriting Wartime Government Bonds]

455
00:25:53,050 --> 00:25:54,100
Yu, are you okay?

456
00:25:55,420 --> 00:25:56,390
Nobody move!

457
00:25:57,550 --> 00:26:02,000
[Nan's Home-style Meal]

458
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,200
What's going on here?

459
00:26:03,420 --> 00:26:05,920
Is it appropriate for so many people
to be fighting in the street?

460
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:07,580
Do you think Macau has no laws?

461
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:08,880
What street fight?

462
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,940
This is clearly a malicious assault!

463
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:12,890
Yes, arrest them!

464
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:13,460
Arrest him!

465
00:26:13,460 --> 00:26:16,330
Catch them!

466
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:19,290
Captain Huang,
what on earth is going on here?

467
00:26:19,290 --> 00:26:21,000
Inspector General Gonçalves,

468
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,730
you came at just the right time.

469
00:26:22,850 --> 00:26:25,160
Didn't you say Macau is a society
ruled by law?

470
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,850
We just issued a law

471
00:26:26,850 --> 00:26:29,550
prohibiting the public sale
of these wartime government bonds.

472
00:26:29,550 --> 00:26:30,750
But what are they doing?

473
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:32,330
What crime should this be?

474
00:26:32,330 --> 00:26:33,750
You're talking nonsense.

475
00:26:33,750 --> 00:26:34,880
The Macau government's ban

476
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:36,290
clearly states

477
00:26:36,290 --> 00:26:38,660
that it only prohibits
financial institutions

478
00:26:38,660 --> 00:26:40,010
from underwriting government bonds.

479
00:26:40,010 --> 00:26:41,920
But Mr. Liang and these youngsters aren't

480
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:43,620
financial institutions, are they?

481
00:26:43,620 --> 00:26:45,020
Inspector General Gonçalves,

482
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:46,790
these thugs committed violence
in the street,

483
00:26:46,790 --> 00:26:48,420
beating teachers and students
from Kiang Wu Elementary School,

484
00:26:48,420 --> 00:26:49,880
as well as these innocent citizens.

485
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:52,530
So many people witnessed it clearly.

486
00:26:52,530 --> 00:26:55,330
Are the police not going to punish
these culprits?

487
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:56,660
Arrest them!

488
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:57,860
Punish the culprits!

489
00:26:57,960 --> 00:27:00,830
I'm sorry, but when the police arrived,

490
00:27:00,830 --> 00:27:02,570
we only saw both sides
fighting each other.

491
00:27:02,570 --> 00:27:03,610
We didn't see anything else!

492
00:27:03,610 --> 00:27:04,470
Nonsense!

493
00:27:04,610 --> 00:27:05,960
Do you even have eyes?

494
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,000
Can you see at all?

495
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,750
If these agents hadn't attacked first,

496
00:27:08,750 --> 00:27:10,110
how could these children
have been injured?

497
00:27:10,110 --> 00:27:11,420
Ask them!

498
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:12,380
Inspector General Gonçalves,

499
00:27:12,380 --> 00:27:14,720
we all saw it clearly with our own eyes.

500
00:27:14,770 --> 00:27:16,400
I've already said.

501
00:27:16,750 --> 00:27:19,760
that the police only saw both sides
fighting in the street.

502
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:22,610
If we're making arrests,
none of you will get away with it!

503
00:27:22,610 --> 00:27:24,500
The government has explicitly prohibited

504
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,430
the sale of Chinese government bonds

505
00:27:26,430 --> 00:27:27,750
and all related promotions.

506
00:27:27,750 --> 00:27:29,750
Anyone who dares to violate this ban

507
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:31,610
will be arrested immediately.

508
00:27:31,980 --> 00:27:34,580
Confiscate
all these promotional materials.

509
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:37,030
Why are you all still gathered here?

510
00:27:37,030 --> 00:27:38,430
Everyone, disperse now!

511
00:27:38,610 --> 00:27:40,080
Anyone who gathers a crowd

512
00:27:40,100 --> 00:27:42,320
and causes trouble again will be arrested!

513
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:43,420
Understood?

514
00:27:43,830 --> 00:27:44,960
Let's go!

515
00:27:45,110 --> 00:27:46,610
Brothers, let's go.

516
00:27:47,850 --> 00:27:49,250
You over there, make way.

517
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:51,930
Did you get hurt?

518
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:52,830
No.

519
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:43,140
[China Government Bonds
Available for Subscription]

520
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:46,650
Mr. Rodrigues.

521
00:28:47,930 --> 00:28:50,390
Mr. Wang has been waiting
for you for a while.

522
00:28:50,610 --> 00:28:52,430
Let's sign the contract now.

523
00:28:58,800 --> 00:29:00,530
Please, Mr. Rodrigues.

524
00:29:07,490 --> 00:29:08,450
I'm sorry.

525
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:11,030
I need a bit more time
to think about this deal.

526
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:12,160
See the gusts out.

527
00:29:13,090 --> 00:29:14,510
Gentlemen, please.

528
00:29:24,540 --> 00:29:25,050
Mr. Liang.

529
00:29:25,050 --> 00:29:25,530
Yes?

530
00:29:26,930 --> 00:29:28,310
The Portuguese Macau government
has sent a notice.

531
00:29:28,310 --> 00:29:30,270
The Government Bond Fundraising Committee
has been banned.

532
00:29:30,270 --> 00:29:32,480
It will be officially shut down tomorrow.

533
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:33,110
Also,

534
00:29:34,730 --> 00:29:36,730
here's a letter sent to your office.

535
00:29:37,110 --> 00:29:37,970
It's unsigned.

536
00:29:41,210 --> 00:29:42,220
[To Liang Yanming
from Kiang Wu Elementary School]

537
00:29:57,130 --> 00:29:59,210
Ah, a petty trick.

538
00:29:59,710 --> 00:30:01,120
An underhanded tactic.

539
00:30:02,070 --> 00:30:05,110
They think this little trick
can intimidate me?

540
00:30:06,190 --> 00:30:08,210
Mr. Liang, we must be cautious.

541
00:30:08,230 --> 00:30:10,500
These people dare to do anything.

542
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:12,120
Yes, Mr. Liang.

543
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:13,700
Where there's life,

544
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,120
there's hope.

545
00:30:15,630 --> 00:30:16,700
At this point,

546
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:18,220
we should stop all actions

547
00:30:18,220 --> 00:30:19,350
and plan carefully.

548
00:30:19,870 --> 00:30:22,870
It's better not
to confront them directly, Mr. Liang.

549
00:30:27,290 --> 00:30:28,240
What did you say?

550
00:30:30,780 --> 00:30:32,610
Plan carefully?

551
00:30:34,510 --> 00:30:37,590
We need to plan carefully?

552
00:30:42,820 --> 00:30:44,820
Will the Japanese stop on their own?

553
00:30:46,030 --> 00:30:47,330
Will they back down?

554
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:51,580
If every Chinese person needs

555
00:30:51,610 --> 00:30:53,000
to plan carefully

556
00:30:53,020 --> 00:30:55,480
whenever trouble strikes,

557
00:31:00,070 --> 00:31:00,740
China

558
00:31:02,650 --> 00:31:03,980
will fall!

559
00:31:08,610 --> 00:31:09,670
It will all be over.

560
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:19,670
Show them out.

561
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:22,670
Show them out!

